===Etymology===
From Moroccan Arabic {{ARchar|[[جلابة|جلّابة]]}} (jellāba).  Compare [[galabiya]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|djellaba|djellabas}}

# A loose fitting, ankle length, hooded [[robe]] worn by men in North Africa.

